    "While such approaches can lead to accurate models, obtaining rigorous clinical annotations is difficult.",
    "Annotations are, however, crucial to properly train supervised models or to further study the significance of certain histomorphologies, e.g. in Johannet et al.",
    "16, immunotherapy response was predicted by selecting tumor regions over lymphocyte-rich or connective tissue regions.",
    "Furthermore, by limiting the study to annotated features, such approaches also limit the potential discovery of new bio-markers.",
    "Finally, such approaches are often described as black-boxes, where interpretation and understanding of how decisions are taken by the network are often difficult, and may affect trust, limiting the ability to take well-informed treatment decisions 17."
